the presentation of the crime scene

43:35.696 --> 43:36.822
to the Travel Inn,

43:36.905 --> 43:39.283
and the type of injuries to the body,

43:39.992 --> 43:42.995
you'd have no doubt
they were inflicted by the same person.

43:45.039 --> 43:48.917
Also, the fact that you're looking
at another prostitute getting killed.

43:51.253 --> 43:54.465
As a profiler, that says one thing.

43:55.799 --> 43:57.885
I got a serial killer. That's it.

44:03.098 --> 44:06.685
The Hotel Seville
was not that far from work.

44:08.520 --> 44:11.065
We called it "slaughter at the Seville."

44:12.483 --> 44:14.360
And that's exactly what it was.

44:16.654 --> 44:20.491
One morning,
Richard and I were sitting at the console,

44:21.950 --> 44:24.787
and Cottingham
was in his chair rocking away,

44:25.371 --> 44:29.041
and one of our peripheral operators
came in, Bob,

44:29.124 --> 44:32.670
with the newspaper in his hand,
and it was on the front page.

44:34.338 --> 44:37.007
And Bob threw it down
on the console and said,

44:37.091 --> 44:40.844
"What sick son of a bitch
could do something like this?"

44:41.512 --> 44:44.306
Cottingham's rocking back and forth
in his chair,

44:44.932 --> 44:47.601
and he looked up at Bob,
and he said, "Bob,

44:48.185 --> 44:50.396
could've been you, could've been me."
